  "prompt": "Why was the Adidas cotton deodorant discontinued? What did customers think of it?",
  "response": "The specific reasons for the discontinuation of **Adidas Cotton Deodorant** are not publicly documented by Adidas, but product discontinuations generally occur due to factors like declining sales, shifts in consumer preferences, or the company focusing on newer or more profitable product lines. In some cases, ingredients, formulations, or branding strategies may also lead to a product being phased out.\n\n### Customer Opinions:\nCustomer feedback on **Adidas Cotton Deodorant** was generally mixed, as is common with personal care products. Here\u2019s a summary of what customers often mentioned:\n\n1. **Positive Feedback:**\n   - Many users appreciated its **light, fresh scent**, which was considered subtle and non-overpowering.\n   - It was praised for being **gentle on the skin**, especially for those with sensitivity to stronger fragrances or alcohol-based deodorants.\n   - The **cotton-themed fragrance** was seen as unique and appealing, evoking a clean, fresh feeling.\n\n2. **Negative Feedback:**\n   - Some customers felt it was **not long-lasting** and required reapplication throughout the day.\n   - Others found the **scent too mild** and not strong enough for heavy use or intense physical activity.\n   - There were occasional complaints about the **packaging or formula changes** over time.\n\n### Discontinuation Impact:\nWhen the product was discontinued, some loyal customers expressed disappointment on forums and social media, as they had come to rely on its specific scent and formulation. It remains a nostalgic product for some, with discussions occasionally resurfacing in online communities about its absence from the market.\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for alternatives, Adidas continues to offer a range of deodorants with different fragrances and formulations, though the \"Cotton\" variant is no longer available.",
